you could actually
do something for me.

15:16.105 --> 15:19.108
I need a fresh financial
write-up on Avi Drexler.

15:19.238 --> 15:20.936
Specifically, any large
cash deposits he's made

15:21.023 --> 15:22.763
into personal accounts.

15:22.894 --> 15:24.330
Is this about your missing guns?

15:24.461 --> 15:25.766
Sooner the better, please.

15:25.897 --> 15:27.377
Enjoy the wedding.

15:37.604 --> 15:39.563
[door opens]

15:42.174 --> 15:43.480
[door closes]

15:43.610 --> 15:45.699
Man, that shit
ain't never gonna work.

15:45.873 --> 15:48.354
How you know?
You try it?

15:48.485 --> 15:51.836
Ain't nobody ever stuck no
banana in no exhaust pipe.

15:51.923 --> 15:55.666
That's the goofiest shit
I ever heard.

15:55.796 --> 15:58.103
Hey, Rows, you cool we go get
some bananas, try that shit out?

15:59.931 --> 16:02.368
You try sticking anything up
my motherfucking tailpipe,

16:02.542 --> 16:05.415
that'd be the last
motherfucking thing you do.

16:06.982 --> 16:09.375
Best movie of all time.
All right?

16:09.506 --> 16:12.291
Soundtrack is hot.
Eddie Murphy hilarious.

16:12.422 --> 16:14.511
Shit cool as hell.

16:14.641 --> 16:16.295
Man, that shit bunk.

16:16.469 --> 16:20.082
Y'all crazy. Don't know shit
about no good movie.

16:20.256 --> 16:21.605
CORNROWS:
Hey!

16:21.735 --> 16:22.954
Hey, hold up!

16:24.086 --> 16:26.088
Hey, hold...
Look at this shit.

16:26.218 --> 16:28.046
Mm!

16:29.700 --> 16:32.007
Damn, girl!

16:32.094 --> 16:33.747
Whoo!

16:33.878 --> 16:35.488
Angels must be real.

16:35.619 --> 16:37.882
-KIRBY: I see you, girl.
-CORNROWS: Hey, that shit hurt?

16:37.969 --> 16:39.623
-What up, baby?
-When you fell from heaven?

16:39.753 --> 16:43.061
SKULLY:
Nigga, get your ass
back over here.

16:43.192 --> 16:46.543
It's not exactly
the brass ring, is it? Hmm.

16:46.717 --> 16:50.503
FRANKLIN:
It's like the man said,
it's a start, right?

16:50.634 --> 16:52.897
I mean, think about it, Mama.

16:53.071 --> 16:56.422
You there, on opening Sunday,

16:56.553 --> 16:59.730
new hat, new suit.

16:59.860 --> 17:02.080
Your name up there on
the wall of benefactors

17:02.211 --> 17:04.300
-for everybody to see.
-They don't put people

17:04.430 --> 17:06.302
who provide loans on that wall,
Franklin.

17:06.432 --> 17:09.218
Well, then we'll
make a donation, too.

17:09.348 --> 17:12.438
I mean, pretty soon you gonna
be lunchin' at Wilfandel.

17:12.569 --> 17:13.787
[laughs]

17:13.918 --> 17:15.485
Ain't that what you wanted?

17:17.139 --> 17:19.489
Just don't forget why we're
doing this in the first place.

17:21.143 --> 17:23.580
Well, we're doing
everything we wanted to do.

17:23.710 --> 17:27.453
We're providing safe,
affordable housing.

17:27.627 --> 17:30.152
We're extending loans to
people in our neighborhoods,

17:30.326 --> 17:32.371
bringing ownership back
to Black homes

17:32.545 --> 17:34.243
and businesses back
into our neighborhoods.

17:34.373 --> 17:36.158
And not to mention
single-handedly

17:36.288 --> 17:37.811
putting a stop to decades,

17:37.942 --> 17:40.379
if not fucking centuries,
of systematic racism.

17:40.510 --> 17:42.381
-Calm down, Franklin.
-I'm-I'm...

17:42.555 --> 17:44.688
I'm calm, but damn, Mama,
why has it

17:44.818 --> 17:46.907
always got to be a problem?
Why is nothing ever good enough?

17:47.038 --> 17:49.040
Because the one promise
you made me,

17:49.171 --> 17:51.260
the promise I actually
need you to keep,

17:51.390 --> 17:53.175
you're completely ignoring.

17:55.002 --> 17:59.094
I didn't bring Paul Davis into
our lives to improve my station.

17:59.181 --> 18:01.096
I did it to get you
off the street

18:01.183 --> 18:03.185
and into
legitimate business deals.

18:03.315 --> 18:05.491
[laughs]:
"Legitimate business deals."

18:05.622 --> 18:08.494
Ma, where were we today?
Please, tell me, where were we?

18:08.625 --> 18:10.322
In a rock house?

18:12.716 --> 18:15.632
No, we was at a country club
eating lobster salad,

18:15.762 --> 18:18.635
and now we're investing
in a church.

18:20.245 --> 18:23.509
-What more do you want?
-I want to know how long.

18:23.640 --> 18:26.773
How long before
it's all we're doing?

18:26.860 --> 18:29.950
Before we can truly trade men
like Reed Thompson for men

18:30.081 --> 18:34.085
like Paul Davis-- the clean exit
that you promised me.

18:34.216 --> 18:37.393
Oh, what-what do you want?
What, you want an exact date?

18:37.523 --> 18:39.090
Considering the circumstances,

18:39.221 --> 18:40.787
I don't think
it's too much to ask.

18:41.919 --> 18:44.226
You want to make me happy?

18:44.356 --> 18:46.576
Get me off your back?

18:46.663 --> 18:49.796
Give me some reason to
believe that we can...

18:49.883 --> 18:52.538
actually make it
out of this intact.

18:54.105 --> 18:57.239
Until then,
none of this means anything.

19:06.378 --> 19:08.424
♪

19:16.388 --> 19:18.434
[Gustavo speaks Spanish]

19:19.913 --> 19:22.307
With their grandparents,
while I get the house ready.

19:24.570 --> 19:27.486
Every day my mother prays
to Nuestra Señora de Guadalupe

19:27.617 --> 19:29.923
so that they don't die
of a broken heart.

19:36.495 --> 19:38.062
Did you get them?

19:40.630 --> 19:41.848
The people who did this?

19:48.159 --> 19:50.292
They'll be back here tomorrow,
by dinnertime.

19:57.951 --> 19:59.518
They ask about you.

19:59.692 --> 20:01.607
Cedro, especially.

20:01.738 --> 20:03.609
[Gustavo speaks Spanish]

20:04.871 --> 20:07.091
Toma.

20:08.179 --> 20:10.268
Whatever you need.

20:10.399 --> 20:12.488
No mames, cabrón.

20:13.489 --> 20:14.838
It's mejorif I stay away.

20:14.968 --> 20:16.274
For who?

20:17.449 --> 20:18.885
For them.

20:19.016 --> 20:21.192
[scoffs]

20:21.323 --> 20:24.195
You-you think I want this?

20:24.369 --> 20:26.893
Put my life on hold
to raise my sister's kids?

20:37.861 --> 20:40.124
[door opens]

20:40.298 --> 20:42.344
[door closes]

20:46.304 --> 20:47.697
IRENE:
Hi, is Tony Marino around?

20:47.784 --> 20:49.786
My name's Irene Abe,
I'm a reporter

20:49.916 --> 20:52.005
-with The Herald Examiner.
-Well, could you

20:52.179 --> 20:54.443
tell me who Mr. Marino's
direct supervisor is?

20:54.573 --> 20:57.184
Mrs. Marino,
Irene Abe, Herald Examiner.

20:57.315 --> 20:59.535
WILSON:
Did Agent Marino keep
an office here in town?

20:59.665 --> 21:01.754
IRENE:
Is your, uh, mommy around,
sweetie?

21:01.885 --> 21:03.669
WILSON:
Uh, Herald Examiner.
Yes, we are still a newspaper.

21:03.800 --> 21:05.758
-Um, I've been holding.
-I just,

21:05.889 --> 21:07.847
-I just need a contact,
um, any name.
-What can you answer?

21:07.934 --> 21:09.284
Marino.

21:09.371 --> 21:11.111
M-A-R-I-N-O.

21:11.242 --> 21:12.852
WILSON:
How is that a subject
you're not allowed

21:12.983 --> 21:14.114
-to broach?
-When was the last
time he showed up?

21:14.245 --> 21:16.116
You can't answer that either?

21:16.247 --> 21:17.944
"Fuck off"?
[laughs]

21:18.075 --> 21:20.512
Can I quote you on that?

21:20.599 --> 21:22.340
[sighs]

21:23.950 --> 21:25.517
[exhales]

21:45.363 --> 21:48.540
Be honest,
you sleep in here sometimes?

21:48.714 --> 21:50.499
No.

21:53.153 --> 21:54.851
Let's hear it.

21:54.981 --> 21:58.855
Got this DEA agent I can't find.

21:58.985 --> 22:01.684
Handler of the other
missing agent I told you about.

22:01.814 --> 22:05.340
Tried his office, home,
his parents, his sister...

22:05.427 --> 22:06.863
I reached out
to an undercover once,

22:06.993 --> 22:08.299
didn't get back to me for weeks.

22:08.430 --> 22:10.083
You eventually get
the story out?

22:10.257 --> 22:11.868
After the Postran it.

22:11.998 --> 22:15.524
I wish I had better
words of wisdom for you,

22:15.698 --> 22:18.614
but it's late,
and "Keep pushing your story

22:18.744 --> 22:21.312
and something's gonna pop"
is the best I have.

22:21.443 --> 22:24.228
Unless...

22:24.402 --> 22:26.883
What about
that man at the shelter?

22:27.013 --> 22:28.537
Saint's father?

22:30.626 --> 22:33.846
Former Panther,
drug dealer for a son...

22:33.977 --> 22:36.240
That is a guilt shelter.

22:36.327 --> 22:40.113
Keep working that angle,
follow the money.

22:40.287 --> 22:42.246
At least it'll keep you busy.

22:45.423 --> 22:48.121
[stove clicking]

22:48.252 --> 22:50.341
Oh, boy.

22:50.472 --> 22:54.127
-What's all this?
-Oh, bookkeeping.

22:54.258 --> 22:55.912
Moving some things around

22:56.086 --> 22:58.436
now that we're
in business with Davis.

22:58.567 --> 23:01.918
Oh. Well, guess that luncheon
went pretty well.

23:02.048 --> 23:04.399
You guys toast to the Mosleys?

23:07.227 --> 23:09.404
Paul Davis is a snake.

23:09.491 --> 23:11.493
Came up in the jungle.

23:11.580 --> 23:14.496
He might've been that way,
but he's a businessman now.

23:14.670 --> 23:18.238
Different kind of snake,
but it still slithers.

23:18.369 --> 23:19.936
You know, I just want you to
know who you're cozying up to.

23:20.110 --> 23:22.808
If cozying up to a snake helps
make sure I never get thrown

23:22.939 --> 23:25.594
into the back of a police car
or watch my son being driven

23:25.724 --> 23:28.031
off in one, then that's
exactly what I will do.

23:28.161 --> 23:29.598
And what you gonna do when
that snake tries to bite you?

23:29.728 --> 23:31.251
Then I will chop
his goddamn head off

23:31.382 --> 23:32.992
and move on to the next one.

23:37.214 --> 23:39.956
All right. God.

23:41.523 --> 23:42.785
[dish rattles]

23:42.872 --> 23:45.483
I'm sorry.

23:45.614 --> 23:48.225
I know you're just doing
what you can.

23:50.967 --> 23:53.448
Come on, eat with me.

23:55.362 --> 23:56.668
TEDDY:
Whiskey, neat, please.

23:56.755 --> 23:59.976
[soft piano music playing]

24:00.106 --> 24:03.066
This is an interesting choice
for someone who doesn't drink.

24:03.196 --> 24:04.763
[Franklin chuckles]

24:04.937 --> 24:07.723
Yeah, figured seeing as
there's no product

24:07.853 --> 24:10.508
being exchanged,
might be nice to meet somewhere

24:10.639 --> 24:12.118
without graffiti and rats,
right?

24:12.205 --> 24:13.729
So here we are.

24:15.208 --> 24:16.862
We about to have a talk?

24:16.993 --> 24:19.082
It's not you, it's me?

24:19.212 --> 24:20.953
[short chuckle]
I've got, um, a question.

24:21.084 --> 24:22.477
It's a little delicate.

24:24.304 --> 24:25.480
Conflict in Nicaragua.

24:27.133 --> 24:30.223
How much longer you think
the good ol' USA stays involved?

24:30.354 --> 24:33.662
Why, I wonder,
would you be asking me that?

24:33.792 --> 24:37.579
Seems my fate's tied
to your covert war, right?

24:37.709 --> 24:40.582
I mean, the war ends...

24:40.756 --> 24:44.673
your need for my services
suddenly goes away.

24:44.803 --> 24:46.022
So, you want to know
how much longer

24:46.152 --> 24:47.893
we're gonna be in business.

24:48.024 --> 24:51.114
Shelf life in my line
of work's pretty limited.

24:51.244 --> 24:53.159
I need to plan ahead.

24:55.553 --> 24:58.251
If there was an operation like
the one you're talking about,

24:58.338 --> 25:00.340
what I would tell you is that
trying to win a guerrilla war

25:00.471 --> 25:02.560
in a third world country
is a little bit like trying

25:02.691 --> 25:04.562
to catch a fastball
with your teeth.

25:04.693 --> 25:06.085
Thank you.

25:08.740 --> 25:12.048
You, um, you been
aiding the Contras

25:12.178 --> 25:14.833
for about five years now,
as far as I can tell, right?

25:15.007 --> 25:17.183
Sure, but it could go on
another four, six, easy.

25:21.623 --> 25:25.104
If I was being honest
with you...

25:26.889 --> 25:29.935
...any date that I give you
right now is either a bad guess

25:30.066 --> 25:32.416
or it's complete bullshit.

25:32.503 --> 25:34.418
You just have to keep
doing what you're doing,

25:34.592 --> 25:36.463
solving problems.

25:36.594 --> 25:39.466
If I catch a glimpse of anything
that looks like a finish line,

25:39.597 --> 25:41.599
I promise
you'll be the first one to know.

25:41.730 --> 25:44.602
What if I doubled my footprint?

25:45.821 --> 25:49.564
More money for you,
more money for Nicaragua.

25:51.391 --> 25:53.524
Time frame go down then?

25:53.655 --> 25:56.962
More money means more resources,
resources win wars.

25:59.182 --> 26:00.618
To winning wars.

26:03.229 --> 26:04.796
[Franklin chuckles]

26:08.017 --> 26:09.409
WANDA:
Fuck off me, bitch!

26:09.540 --> 26:11.542
-[monitor beeping]
-Lee, they trying to kill me.

26:11.716 --> 26:13.065
LEON:
Ain't nobody trying to kill you.

26:13.196 --> 26:14.763
Then why is the machine beeping?

26:14.893 --> 26:17.243
-Hey, I'm-a wait downstairs.
-All right.

26:17.330 --> 26:20.116
WANDA:
Oh, shit. What's in that needle?

26:20.246 --> 26:21.683
This trick ain't even no doctor.

26:21.770 --> 26:23.119
Wanda, these people are trying
to help you, all right?

26:23.293 --> 26:24.903
And you just talking shit
to get yourself thrown out

26:25.034 --> 26:26.862
so you can be back
on the street smoking.

26:27.863 --> 26:28.820
Thank you.

26:30.126 --> 26:31.997
What's in that needle
gonna help you

26:32.128 --> 26:34.217
push that shit out your body.

26:34.347 --> 26:36.785
I paid the hospital to let you
stay longer, all right?

26:36.915 --> 26:38.613
Give you a second chance.

26:40.266 --> 26:42.007
You get yourself bounced,

26:42.181 --> 26:43.269
that's it, I don't want
nothing to do with you.

26:43.400 --> 26:44.488
You hear me?

26:49.449 --> 26:50.842
Stay with me, Lee.

26:50.929 --> 26:53.018
I don't know, I got shit to do.

26:53.149 --> 26:54.498
Please.

26:54.672 --> 26:56.239
Nobody else coming.

26:57.544 --> 26:59.634
Just... just stay for tonight.

27:16.085 --> 27:17.826
♪

27:20.959 --> 27:22.744
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

27:31.927 --> 27:35.626
We expanding.
It's time we grew past L.A.,

27:35.757 --> 27:37.193
start spreading this business.

27:37.323 --> 27:40.283
The question is,
where do we start first?

27:40.413 --> 27:43.068
Rock already found
its way to New York.

27:43.199 --> 27:45.636
Cubans and Colombians,
they running shit out there

27:45.767 --> 27:47.812
and into D.C.

27:47.943 --> 27:49.118
It's gonna make it hard
to get a foothold.

27:50.423 --> 27:52.208
Italians, they runnin' Chicago.

27:52.382 --> 27:53.905
Don't shit happen
without their say-so.

27:53.992 --> 27:56.865
We can start by targeting
mid-level cities.

27:56.995 --> 27:59.998
Less problems.
Build out from there.

28:00.172 --> 28:02.827
FRANKLIN:
One in particular
you got in mind?

28:02.958 --> 28:05.090
LOUIE:
Girl I grew up with,
her and her man.

28:05.221 --> 28:07.005
They in Little Rock.
We can start there.

28:07.092 --> 28:08.659
You sure the best time
for this is right now?

28:08.790 --> 28:10.443
When we still got problems
in L.A.?

28:10.574 --> 28:11.575
That's exactly why
we need to expand.

28:11.706 --> 28:13.403
Yeah, more fucking headaches.

28:13.533 --> 28:15.013
Why you can't just
tell the white boy

28:15.187 --> 28:16.754
that we gonna decrease the buy

28:16.885 --> 28:18.451
until we get
Manboy and Skully straight?

28:18.625 --> 28:20.932
That way I can get back
to my shop.

28:21.019 --> 28:23.587
We're not telling Reed
we're buying less.

28:23.761 --> 28:25.371
Why not?

28:27.634 --> 28:29.985
What, y'all scared to tell
the hee-haw white boy?

28:30.115 --> 28:33.466
We're not doing that, Unc, okay?
We're not moving backwards.

28:33.640 --> 28:36.034
Louie, make them calls.

28:36.121 --> 28:38.080
If Little Rock interested,
y'all two go out there.

28:39.429 --> 28:41.170
Take a bird.
Teach 'em how to rock it up.

28:41.257 --> 28:43.041
Give 'em
that first taste for free.

28:43.215 --> 28:44.651
Same shit we did here.

28:44.782 --> 28:47.698
Take Peaches with you,
if he's up for it.

28:47.872 --> 28:50.614
This how we stay safe,
stay out of trouble.

28:50.745 --> 28:52.616
Grow without exposure.

28:52.703 --> 28:55.271
It'll work, Unc.
It'll work.

28:59.057 --> 29:01.059
LOUIE:
Um, I meant to tell you,

29:01.190 --> 29:03.845
she came by yesterday
and asked for a job.

29:03.975 --> 29:06.151
[chuckles] A job?
What, here at the club?

29:06.282 --> 29:07.936
Yeah. She got experience.

29:08.066 --> 29:10.068
Figure she can hold it down
when I'm gone.

29:10.242 --> 29:13.202
-Mm.
-That a problem?

29:13.289 --> 29:14.943
FRANKLIN:
Nah. Just surprised, that's all.

29:15.073 --> 29:16.640
LOUIE:
Figure you sleep with her,

29:16.771 --> 29:18.033
I can trust her.

29:18.163 --> 29:19.817
Was I wrong?

29:23.429 --> 29:24.300
LEON:
Three addresses?

29:24.430 --> 29:26.171
That's it?

29:26.302 --> 29:28.173
You asked where he goes
outside of Inglewood.

29:28.304 --> 29:29.871
That's your answer.

29:30.001 --> 29:31.394
What's this spot in Gardena?

29:31.524 --> 29:34.092
Terrence's grandmother's house.

29:34.223 --> 29:35.877
Skully's real name is Terrence?

29:36.007 --> 29:37.966
That nigga look like a Terrence.

29:38.140 --> 29:41.186
REGGIE:
Grandma's house is the only
place he visited more than once.

29:41.317 --> 29:44.015
Was there maybe five minutes
each time.

29:44.102 --> 29:47.062
Took a bag in,
brought no bag out.

29:47.192 --> 29:49.107
That's probably where
he keeping all his money.

29:49.238 --> 29:51.153
-It'd be smart.
-Yeah.

29:51.283 --> 29:53.329
Outside his turf, so people
don't fuck with it.

29:53.503 --> 29:57.115
Ooh, gentlemen, this feels
like a private exchange.

29:57.246 --> 29:58.029
You're gonna need to...

30:00.118 --> 30:01.511
...take it outside.

30:01.641 --> 30:03.339
Unless there's something else
I can do for you.

30:03.469 --> 30:04.819
It's all good.

30:11.390 --> 30:12.696
[door opens]

30:14.480 --> 30:15.351
[door closes]

30:15.525 --> 30:18.006
[baby crying]

30:23.054 --> 30:25.361
[indistinct chatter]

30:25.491 --> 30:27.493
Where you been, man?

30:27.624 --> 30:29.452
And where's the diapers?

30:29.582 --> 30:31.541
-Let me just sit down
for a second.
-You smoked the money?

30:31.671 --> 30:32.890
-She's sleeping
in her own piss, man.
-You in my business?

30:33.021 --> 30:34.239
-How could you do that?
-Hey, hey, hey.

30:34.370 --> 30:35.980
-Wait a minute. Wait a minute!
-You so smart?!

30:36.111 --> 30:37.808
ALTON:
Hey, what's-what's going on,
Dwayne?

30:37.939 --> 30:39.679
He's supposed to be
getting diapers.

30:39.810 --> 30:41.681
-Dwayne...
-Out smoking instead.

30:41.812 --> 30:42.944
I know you better
watch your mouth.

30:43.074 --> 30:44.380
-That's your daughter, man.
-John, wait.

30:44.510 --> 30:46.077
Dwayne, listen.

30:46.164 --> 30:48.036
I'll go get you some diapers.

30:48.210 --> 30:49.472
In the meantime,
why don't you go get you

30:49.602 --> 30:50.865
some of that orange chicken.

30:52.083 --> 30:53.476
That's one of
your favorites, huh?

30:53.606 --> 30:55.173
Yeah, have Ms. Leonard...
Hey, Ms. Leonard,

30:55.304 --> 30:57.306
make this young man
a plate of that orange chicken

30:57.393 --> 30:58.524
that he loves so much.

31:00.178 --> 31:01.876
[baby continues crying]

31:07.490 --> 31:10.145
You can't come in here
like this, John.

31:11.624 --> 31:15.063
I'm not gonna
raise my voice at you,

31:15.193 --> 31:16.847
but this is the last time.

31:17.021 --> 31:18.588
You do it again and you're out.

31:18.718 --> 31:20.198
I'm sorry. I just, I...

31:20.329 --> 31:22.418
Listen to me, John.
Listen to me.

31:22.548 --> 31:25.029
You need to
get yourself together.

31:25.160 --> 31:26.901
You gonna mess around
and lose your kids, man.

31:28.815 --> 31:31.122
And you will
regret that forever.

31:36.214 --> 31:38.303
-Mm-hmm.
-Go and get you
something to eat.

31:42.394 --> 31:44.092
And hey,

31:44.222 --> 31:45.702
maybe don't sit
next to Dwayne, okay?

31:45.789 --> 31:47.008
All right.

31:50.663 --> 31:52.274
[sighs]

31:57.192 --> 31:59.890
What can Edgewood Shelters
do for you?

32:00.021 --> 32:00.935
I was in the neighborhood.

32:01.022 --> 32:02.458
Thought we'd talk
a little more--

32:02.588 --> 32:05.243
about you, the shelter,

32:05.374 --> 32:07.245
things you and your wife
do for the community.

32:07.419 --> 32:09.247
I never mentioned a wife.

32:09.421 --> 32:12.685
And I haven't worn my
wedding band since I sobered up.

32:12.859 --> 32:14.035
I looked you up, okay?

32:14.209 --> 32:16.124
-Hmm.
-You're fascinating.

32:16.298 --> 32:18.256
I think you'd make
an amazing profile--

32:18.430 --> 32:20.258
Black Panther, the streets,
a shelter...

32:20.345 --> 32:22.608
Yeah, yeah, yeah. How do you
know a reporter's lying?

32:22.782 --> 32:25.350
'Cause her lips are moving.

32:25.524 --> 32:28.701
Don't come back here looking to
chitchat or for any more stories

32:28.832 --> 32:30.225
'cause you'll find neither.

32:43.412 --> 32:45.718
[insects chirping]

32:45.849 --> 32:47.851
[brakes squeak]

32:51.289 --> 32:52.464
[engine turns off]

32:52.595 --> 32:53.596
Thanks, Lurp.

32:55.380 --> 32:57.861
See you in the morning.
Say around 9:00?

32:59.645 --> 33:01.386
Can't, sir.

33:01.517 --> 33:04.868
All right. Just the morning
or you need the whole day?

33:06.826 --> 33:08.872
This is as far as I go.

33:11.614 --> 33:13.181
I'm done.

33:13.311 --> 33:15.748
[laughs softly]
What?

33:15.922 --> 33:18.099
What the fuck you mean, "done"?

33:18.229 --> 33:20.666
I thought I could handle this.

33:20.753 --> 33:23.234
Told myself the money
was worth it, but...

33:24.975 --> 33:27.238
...I wasn't prepared
for all the bloodshed.

33:31.025 --> 33:33.201
I mean, war overseas
is one thing.

33:36.378 --> 33:39.033
But our people killing
each other in our streets...

33:42.123 --> 33:44.255
Hey, you got to draw a line
somewhere.

33:47.693 --> 33:49.347
This is mine.

33:49.478 --> 33:50.870
Okay.

33:52.829 --> 33:54.657
I hear that.

33:54.787 --> 33:56.006
I do.

33:56.137 --> 33:58.226
I mean, shit,

33:58.400 --> 34:00.924
it's not what I wanted either,
you know?

34:01.055 --> 34:04.058
But now is not the time to walk.

34:06.147 --> 34:08.627
So here's what we gonna do.
I'm-a double your pay,

34:08.758 --> 34:10.542
you gonna gut up, we gonna
get through this rough patch,

34:10.673 --> 34:12.457
and then you have
my permission to go off

34:12.631 --> 34:15.591
and join the motherfucking
Peace Corps for all I care.

34:15.765 --> 34:18.072
But you will not abandon me
right now.

34:20.161 --> 34:21.727
Not right now.

34:24.948 --> 34:27.037
I'm sorry, sir.

34:31.694 --> 34:33.739
♪

34:44.750 --> 34:46.491
[Franklin grunts]

35:00.853 --> 35:02.855
[engine starts]

35:18.654 --> 35:20.221
[drops keys]

35:22.005 --> 35:24.877
Don't scream.
Don't run.

35:26.314 --> 35:29.230
My name is Tony Marino.
You're looking for me.

35:30.796 --> 35:33.147
Took the liberty of looking
through your notes.

35:34.452 --> 35:35.975
You should really be
keeping these in

35:36.106 --> 35:37.890
a secure off-site location.

35:38.064 --> 35:40.545
In case some asshole
breaks into my house?

35:40.676 --> 35:42.591
You think you know
the story you're telling.

35:45.594 --> 35:47.770
You don't have a clue.

35:51.077 --> 35:53.123
It isn't Franklin Saint.

35:53.254 --> 35:55.691
And it also
isn't Lorena Cardenas, who,

35:55.865 --> 35:59.347
as much as it pains me to say,
I'm sure is dead.

35:59.521 --> 36:03.438
The real story is
who's protecting Saint and why.

36:04.830 --> 36:08.051
If I have to guess,
we might be here awhile.

36:10.227 --> 36:12.098
I did some looking into you.

36:12.229 --> 36:14.275
What little
I could find, anyway.

36:14.405 --> 36:16.494
Your family put into
the internment camp

36:16.668 --> 36:18.061
at Manzanar
when you were little.

36:18.235 --> 36:20.150
College at Berkeley.

36:20.281 --> 36:22.805
Then back to L.A., the Times...

36:22.935 --> 36:25.851
That piece you wrote on
the second Owens Valley aqueduct

36:25.938 --> 36:27.070
that got you fired.

36:27.157 --> 36:28.724
Your estranged husband
Henry Nelson,

36:28.898 --> 36:30.291
daughter Jane...

36:30.378 --> 36:32.597
All right. What the fuck?
What are you doing?

36:32.728 --> 36:35.165
Trying to figure out if I give
this to you, if you're capable

36:35.339 --> 36:37.298
of following it through
to the end.

36:37.385 --> 36:40.475
If it's true and it matters,
I'll get it in print.

36:40.605 --> 36:43.086
Getting it to print is only
the beginning, Irene.

36:49.527 --> 36:52.965
Ask yourself,
who has the power to derail

36:53.139 --> 36:56.491
a DEA investigation,
then dissolve the murder charges

36:56.621 --> 36:58.319
when the key witness
is a federal agent?

36:58.493 --> 37:00.103
Ronald Reagan.

37:00.277 --> 37:01.539
Getting warmer.

37:12.246 --> 37:13.986
Motherfucker.

37:14.160 --> 37:16.250
-Is this real?
-Yes.

37:17.642 --> 37:19.905
Now all you need to do
is prove it.

37:20.079 --> 37:22.430
No. No.
No, no, no.

37:22.604 --> 37:24.693
I need to hear this from you,
all of it, right now...

37:24.780 --> 37:26.477
I'll stay for an hour,
walk you through everything,

37:26.564 --> 37:27.478
but we never met.

37:28.871 --> 37:31.221
That's my deal.

37:31.352 --> 37:34.920
Our own CIA is bringing cocaine
into the U.S.

37:35.007 --> 37:37.009
It's a story of a lifetime,
Irene.

37:37.183 --> 37:38.707
You want it or not?

37:46.889 --> 37:48.325
FATBACK:
Man, let's get out of here.

37:48.456 --> 37:50.022
LEON:
Hell no.

37:50.196 --> 37:51.894
Nigga, you heard the man.

37:52.024 --> 37:54.375
This the only place Skully been
seen at multiple times.

37:54.505 --> 37:57.595
Yeah, but my sciatica, nigga.

37:57.769 --> 37:59.467
Why don't we just get
my big cuz and them over here

37:59.597 --> 38:01.251
to watch this shit?
They ain't doing nothing

38:01.382 --> 38:02.600
but sitting up in the projects
any damn way.

38:02.731 --> 38:04.559
Hell no.

38:10.129 --> 38:12.523
[bottles clinking]

38:21.010 --> 38:22.707
[vehicle approaching]

38:24.709 --> 38:26.450
[tires screech]

38:26.581 --> 38:29.410
♪ Your love is like
a merry-go-round...♪

38:29.540 --> 38:31.368
Hey, hey, is that
fucking Leon in there?

38:31.499 --> 38:33.414
That's Skully's people
right there, nigga.

38:35.198 --> 38:37.287
[indistinct shouting]

38:39.637 --> 38:43.728
♪ Your love is like
a merry-go-round...♪

38:43.859 --> 38:45.556
[steam hissing]

38:47.515 --> 38:50.648
[men coughing, groaning]

38:50.779 --> 38:51.649
No.

38:51.780 --> 38:54.130
No, no, no, no! No, no!

38:58.656 --> 39:00.005
I see you, motherfucker!

39:00.136 --> 39:03.008
[Khadijah screams]

39:03.095 --> 39:05.446
[echoes]:
Oh, my God!

39:05.620 --> 39:09.014
[sobbing]:
My baby! No! No!

39:09.188 --> 39:10.799
Shit.

39:13.018 --> 39:16.326
No! Please, God, no!

39:16.457 --> 39:20.678
Somebody help! My baby!

39:20.852 --> 39:23.681
[sobbing hysterically]

39:23.855 --> 39:26.075
Somebody help me, please!

39:26.205 --> 39:28.773
My baby! My baby!

39:28.947 --> 39:30.471
♪ Your love is like
a merry-go-round...♪

39:30.645 --> 39:32.124
-No!
-FATBACK: Let's fucking go, Lee!

39:32.255 --> 39:34.126
[sirens approaching]

39:34.300 --> 39:36.346
KHADIJAH:
Help me, somebody, please!

39:36.477 --> 39:38.043
FATBACK:
Hey, come on, man.

39:38.130 --> 39:39.349
KHADIJAH:
No!

39:39.480 --> 39:41.830
-[engine starts]
-Oh, my baby!

39:41.917 --> 39:46.051
-Please help! My baby!
-LEON: Fuck! [groans]

39:46.225 --> 39:49.707
KHADIJAH:
No!

39:49.838 --> 39:51.579
[panting]

39:54.495 --> 39:55.931
[echoes]:
Fuck!

